JERVIS BAY ROAD INTERSECTION UPGRADE

Construction work is underway, including major earthworks and embankment construction; bridge works and retaining wall construction; road surface and ramp construction; utility relocations; and drainage upgrades.

Changes to traffic conditions. including lane and shoulder closures, will be in place at various times along the Princes Hwy and other nearby roads as a result of the Jervis Bay intersection upgrade project.

Motorists are advised to allow approximately 5 minutes of additional travel time when traffic control is active.
Portable traffic lights will allow motorists to pass in one direction at a time.
Changed traffic conditions will be in place in various locations on the Great Western Highway between Glenbrook and Katoomba between 8pm and 5am Sunday to Thursday.

Single lane closures will be in place for the eastbound slow lane on McCaffrey Drive and in both directions along Lookout Road between Kookaburra Circuit and Carnley Avenue.

Traffic controllers will be on site to direct motorists.

Motorists are encouraged to take alternative travel options via Lake Road, Main Road, Macquarie Road and Hillsborough Road, when suitable, to reduce the wider network impacts.

arrangementElements.html:
Heavy vehicles with a ground contact or with overall width wider than 3m are advised to contact the project team at least one day ahead of movement on 1800 818 433. Significant delays will occur if failure to contact. 

 

Freight operators are advised the project operates on UHF channel 52 at the Southern Interchange.
